Senate Bill No. 334–Senator Neal
CHAPTER..........
AN ACT relating to correctional institutions; requiring the Director
of the Department of Corrections to submit an annual report
to the Director of the Legislative Counsel Bureau relating to
the employment of offenders; and providing other matters
properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
This bill requires the Director of the Department of Corrections to submit a
report relating to the employment of offenders on or before March 1 of each year to
the Director of the Legislative Counsel Bureau for transmittal to the Senate
Standing Committee on Finance and the Assembly Standing Committee on Ways
and Means during a regular or special session of the Legislature, or the Interim
Finance Committee when the Legislature is not in session. The report must include,
without limitation, the following information relating to the previous year: (1) the
number of offenders who were eligible for employment; (2) the number of
offenders who were employed; (3) the number of offenders who refused
employment; (4) the pay of the offenders who were employed; (5) the educational
attainments of the offenders who were employed; (6) the amount of the deductions
from the accounts of offenders who were employed; and (7) of the offenders who
were employed and who were subsequently released, the percentage of offenders
who found employment following release with the industries in which they were
employed.
